Automobile Insurance System.

The main entities would be
  - Customer -> the one who applies or views the policies
  - Policy -> the records of all types of policies
  - Officer -> the one who manages the policy to a particular customer

The policy can be categorized for different types of vehicles as
  - Light Commercial Vehicles
  - Intermediate Commercial Vehicles
  - Heavy Commercial Vehicles

Customer claims and payments can be separately handled.

Story -- 
Customer is the starting point. A customer registers and gets linked to one or more policies. The customer must exist before any policy can be created.
So, a customer will be able view, apply, review their policies. Accordingly the officer approves and manages their customer's request. One officer can handle many policies.

Policy is the important component of the system. One customer can have multiple policies over time.
It connects the customer and officer together, stores the insurance contract details like premium amount, coverage, start and end dates, and current status.
A variety of policies are provided as depending on the policy type as Third Party, Own Damage or Comprehensive.
Vehicle is directly tied to a policy. Each vehicle can categorised as LCV, ICV, HCV, which are differentiated through breakpoints such as max_load is 7, 12, 12+ respectively. 
